            "text": "We'll move through five galleries. The first gallery focuses on the Franklin Expedition of 1845 — Sir John Franklin's attempt to navigate the Northwest Passage. His two ships, the Erebus and the Terror, were lost with all one hundred and twenty-nine men on board. It remained one of Canada's greatest mysteries until both ships were discovered — the Erebus in 2014 and the Terror in 2016."
